The paper deals with the analysis of reservoir computing systems in the framework of statistical learning theory, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Reservoir computing is a type of neural network, which also makes it relevant to the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the dependence structure of signals, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper deals with the estimation accuracy of reservoir families, which is a topic in statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the consistency of empirical risk minimization, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
